post_text:
Dear George-Little Rock Students, Parents, Staff, and Community,

Today Iowa Governor Kim Reynolds declared Iowa schools closed for the remainder of the 2019-2020 school year. This comes as no surprise as Iowa cases of COVID-19 has not peaked in Iowa. The GLR leadership, teachers and administration, have discussed possible scenarios. Leadership will be meeting on Monday to discuss plans and procedures going forward. Please look to the district website, www.george-littlerock.org, the district Facebook page, https://www.facebook.com/George-Little-Rock-Community-School-District-230125240354744/, and communications through JMC.

Our teachers will continue to serve their students as best we can. Our meal program will continue until further notice.

In the meantime, please continue to practice good health procedures and stay healthy.

Pat O‚ÄôDonnell

Today, Kim Reynolds, Governor of the State of Iowa, extended the closure of schools until April 30, 2020. The George-Little Rock schools will follow the Governor‚Äôs order and will be remain closed with the tentative reopening date of May 4, 2020. If this reopening date does not change, May 1, 2020 will be used as a teacher professional development day in order to prepare for the return of students. Additional information will be forthcoming for students and parents as to how the district will proceed with the delivery of instruction during the closure. Your child‚Äôs teacher will continue sending out instructional materials to students. The Meals program will continue.

Pat O‚ÄôDonnell

post_text: During the school‚Äôs closure, GLR is offering free grab and go meals to students 18 yrs and under starting tomorrow. Delivering meals will also be an option. Please contact the school in advance to sign up for meals and/or delivery service by contacting Colleen Trei at 712-475-3311 ext 127 or ctrei @george-littlerock.org. Please specify how many lunches you will need for your students and if it will be pickup or delivery. Deliveries will need to provide the address too. Meals may be picked up at the front door of George or Little Rock sites from 11 am ‚Äì 12:30 pm. Deliveries will begin at 11:00 with someone required to be home to accept the meal(s). GLR must receive written permission with a signature to deliver meals. Please have a signed permission slip with a signature on the first day of delivery. (Example: GLR has my permission to deliver meals to my house.)

Good Morning! I appreciate everyone's patience as we enter into this difficult time. Notes:
The Board meeting will be held this evening in Little Rock at 5:30 PM. Our intent is to have Lyon County Public health screen visitors.
PT conferences will be by phone or email. More info to come.
Leadership will be meeting this morning to discuss how to feed students that need meals during the closure, ways to keep contact with the educational program, and other various issues going forward.
Thank you,
Pat O'Donnell

post_text: On December 20 the GLR FFA butchered our last 60 birds! The support and help from the community was greatly appreciated. Special thanks to Katie Olson and her family for helping set up and prepare a working assembly line with plucker and scalding pot included! With that being said, the kids learned a lot about the ins and outs of how to properly harvest and process a chicken! If you would like a farm grown FFA raised bird for your freezer please contact Miss Ubben or an FFA member! Birds are $20 with giblets included upon request or $2 for just the giblets!

Red Ribbon week at GLR
The students in grades 8th-12th grade will be having an informational assembly on October 23rd in regards to bringing awareness about the harmful effects from tobacco products/e-cigarettes/and vaping. The presenter is Teri Bos from the Sioux County Community Health Partners and she will be presenting in two sessions during the morning. The 8th/9th/and 10th grade first then followed by the 11th and 12th grade.
